      "rationale": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the screw-rod-vertebral block assembly. QoI values (stiffness, yield force) changed by less than 1.4% between the second-finest and finest mesh, confirming discretization error is well controlled."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual norms below 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error below 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver convergence was monitored for all 11 model instances. Force and displacement residuals converged to specified tolerances without divergence or spurious oscillation. Energy balance confirmed for nonlinear contact steps."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup by a second analyst not involved in primary model construction; checklist-based review completed.",
      "rationale": "Each of the three modeling teams performed internal peer review of boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and load application. Cross-team comparison of setup documentation identified and resolved one minor discrepancy in rod-screw interface friction coefficient."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic with geometric nonlinearity and frictional contact captures dominant physics; plasticity included for yield force prediction.",
      "rationale": "The model employs isotropic linear elasticity with large-deformation kinematics and surface-to-surface frictional contact at the screw-rod interface. Bilinear isotropic hardening is included to capture post-yield behavior. This form is consistent with the physics governing quasi-static ASTM F1717 loading and with prior published models of comparable constructs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from certified material test reports for production-lot Ti-6Al-4V; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of test articles.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and ultimate tensile strength were taken from certified material test reports for the same production lot as the tested constructs. Screw geometry was characterized by coordinate measuring machine on three representative screws. Rod geometry was measured by optical profilometry."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 production-representative constructs tested; sample size sufficient for statistical comparison at 95% confidence.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled from production-representative components and tested across two independent laboratories (N=6 and N=5). Constructs were assembled by trained technicians following the device IFU. Sample size was determined a priori by power analysis targeting 80% power to detect a 10% QoI difference."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions match ASTM F1717 protocol; multiple load levels or configurations desirable for full gradation.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted strictly per ASTM F1717 at a single compression-bending load configuration. While the protocol is standardized and well-controlled, only one test condition was evaluated. This limits the achieved level to Gradation 2, one below the required level. This gap is accepted given that F1717 is the regulatory reference test and multi-condition testing is not standard practice for this submission type."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs (geometry, material, boundary conditions, torque) traceable to measured test article parameters; discrepancies quantified and within 5%.",
      "rationale": "Model geometry and material properties were matched to the specific test articles used in the N=11 experiments. Screw insertion torque was measured during assembly and applied as a preload in the FEA. All input discrepancies between model and experiment were quantified and found to be within 3.8%, well within the 5% threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) within 10% of experimental mean; E/uval < 1.96 for each QoI.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison using the ASME V&V 40 E/uval metric was performed for all three QoIs across all three modeling teams. Maximum E/uval was 1.42 (yield force, FDA model). All percent differences were below 8.5%. Acceptance criteria are met for the ensemble."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the clinical risk of construct failure under physiological loading.",
      "rationale": "The three selected QoIs are the primary mechanical performance metrics specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly relevant to the clinical concern of construct fatigue and fracture. Construct stiffness governs load sharing; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement characterize failure onset and ultimate strength margins."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation test geometry, material, and loading are representative of the COU device and intended use environment.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the identical non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design intended for submission. The ASTM F1717 test configuration is the regulatory reference for spinal implant mechanical performance and is directly representative of the COU. Two independent laboratories were engaged to assess inter-laboratory variability, further strengthening the relevance claim."
    }
